result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

2:33 PM Cases 22CF28 and 22CF55 called together.  Defendant Jaclyn Giikwe Taylor in court.  Attorney Eugene D Harrington in court for Jaclyn Giikwe Taylor.  Attorney James Jay Rennicke Esq in court for State of Wisconsin. Cases on for Plea/Sentencing Hearing.  Def waives all in person hearing KIV.  Agreement is recited by Atty Harrington: def pleading to misdemeanor bond jump; joint recommendation for 1 year probation, costs, sobriety, continued after care, curfew if ordered, employment.  Parties have 7 days to update the Court with jail credit information.  State moves to amend Count 1 of 22CF55 to misdemeanor bond jump, provides basis; Court grants amendment.  Court asks def if they understand the agreement.  Def does.  Court reviews Def's constitutional rights.  Def understands that def is waiving those rights by entering into agreement today.  Court asks Def if they understand Court is not bound by agreement, and could order maximum penalties.  Def understands.  Court asks for plea.  Def enters a plea of Guilty.  Court finds def is making plea knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily.  Court finds a factual basis to accept the plea.  Court finds defendant guilty of amended Count 1 of 22CF55 and orders a JOC; 22CF28 is DRI.  DA asks Court to accept agreement.  Defense attorney asks Court to accept agreement.  Def declines to make a statement to the Court.  
Court orders:
1 yr probation, withheld sentence
Conditions of probation:
$443 court costs. Def to pay $25 per month, 1st payment by end of December to Probation.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Get GED.  Absolute sobriety- No use or possession of any alcohol illegal drugs, paraphernalia, or controlled substances without a valid prescription. Defendant is restricted from any establishments whose primary purpose is the sale of alcohol- such as bars, taverns, beer tents, and liquor stores. Continue with mental health recommendations; take all prescriptions as prescribed.  Curfew at the discretion of her DOC agent.  Gainful employment or be enrolled in higher education.  7 days to provide jail credit.
Appeal rights provided.  DNA to be provided to the Sheriff before leaving the building.  Def to provide prints in 22CF55 to BCSD today.
